Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Goswami!! Brain-melt from Moeen Ali. Nothing more than that. Suddenly he has kicked the door wide open for SRH to come back into the game. Rashid Khan's last over and with AB gone, he decides to play a cute reverse paddle, when he was hitting them so well straight down the ground. Such a low-percentage shot and one must applaud Goswami's take. On the rebound and it was a clear deflection too. Moeen Ali walked as soon as Goswami took it. That shot could potentially send RCB out of the tournament. But Moeen Ali plays that way and has got out many times previously very softly. Fantastic innings nonetheless. Moeen Ali c Goswami b Rashid Khan 65(34) [4s-2 6s-6]

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to de Villiers, out Caught by Dhawan!! Rashid Khan has done the double over AB this season. Got him both times. This wicket the credit has to go to Dhawan. What a catch under extreme pressure. Could mean a difference of 30 easily. de Villiers slogs and doesn't get the elevation, Dhawan at deep backward square was on the edge, but leapt at the right time, caught it and ensured that the left leg didn't trod on the cushion. He raises his finger Ricky Ponting Sydney style to say it's out. Kohli is anxious and cranes his neck out to check whether this is a legal catch. It is and de Villiers walks. Again silence at the Chinnaswamy. 150th wicket for Rashid in T20s. de Villiers c Dhawan b Rashid Khan 69(39) [4s-12 6s-1]

Commentary Text: S Kaul to de Villiers, FOUR, not sure whether it is four or six. de Villiers grits his teeth and it is not a six. Maybe AB thought it didn't go all the way. It has been sent upstairs. Has the ball landed bang on the cushion? After de Villiers lifted a length ball on the stumps towards wide long-on. Still looking. Umpire Chettithody Shamsuddin wants to get this absolutely correct in the third ump's box. They are zooming in and zooming out. Crowd keep waiting. S Ravi does too. To get the orders from above. They could have taken the strategic timeout and got done with it. More than 3 minutes as I type. Finally a decision has been made. It is four. And it is the right call too, one angle showed clearly that the ball bounced in front of the cushions. The game moves on - thankfully

Commentary Text: Rashid Khan to Kohli, out Bowled!! The RCB fans are stunned into deathly silence. Deathly. While Rashid Khan celebrates with a finger-twirling celebration. Kohli doesn't pick Rashid Khan, slogs in hope to a googly which is bowled on a fuller length and sees the stumps re-arranged. Difficult to say whether Rashid Khan has the wood over Kohli - a very small sample size for that. But for sure Rashid has the bragging rights over the RCB skipper. Commentary Text: Moeen Ali to Hales, out Caught by de Villiers!! No way. He didn't just do that. It's all about the Avengers now, but AB is the only one keeping DC alive. A toss-up outside off, Hales gets down the wicket and bottom-hand swats that flat towards deep mid-wicket, seems to have cleared it till the last moment until Superman arrives from Krypton to pluck that out of thin air. Leaps and grabs that one-handed. Absolutely ridiculous. The right foot was in fact extremely close to the rope and he landed on the right foot and had enough balance at the age of 34 to hold on and he was dancing like a teenager. Absolute magic. Hales c de Villiers b Moeen Ali 37(24) [4s-2 6s-3]

Commentary Text: U Yadav to Hales, 1 run, what a catch by Southee at deep square leg. Hales uses a most commonly uttered English expletive as he rues his bad luck. Hang on. It has been referred upstairs. Soft signal is out. They are checking for it. Are the fingers under the ball? Looks like it. Again umpire Chettithody Shamsuddin in the hotseat. Who is the third umpire. And he has ruled it not out. Kohli is aghast. As is Southee. The RCB captain isn't happy at all. Has a word with the umpire. But they ask him to get on with it. Pulled flat and looked like Southee who came forward and dived low to catch it, had the fingers under the ball. Not to the third umpire. Even Clarke on air was confident that it was out. He reckoned that these slow-mo replays create an illusion that the ball is grounded. Anyway Hales gets a life. Will this moment turn out to be a turning point? Let's wait and watch...
